xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>pāka-</w><gloss><q>зрелость</q></gloss></mentioned>. Однако основное значение последнего слова — ‘варка’, ‘кипячение’ — плохо согласуется с %ifag%i. Ближе семантически стоит <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>pāk</w><gloss><q>omnis</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/><gloss><q>totus</q></gloss></mentioned>,  (наряду с <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>pāk</w><gloss><q>чистый</q></gloss></mentioned>). Не исключена возможность образования из *ap-āka- от ap- ‘достигать’. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_Шегрен"/><biblScope>68</biblScope></bibl>: <mentioned xml:lang="ar"><lang/><w>faqat</w><gloss><q>только</q></gloss></mentioned>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">G. %sMorgenstierne%s (<bibl><author>Morgenstierne</author><ref target="#ref_NTS"/><biblScope>XII 267</biblScope></bibl>) relates it to <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>pāka-</w><gloss><q>maturity</q></gloss></mentioned>. However, the main meaning of the latter word — ‘cooking’, ‘boiling’ — does not agree well with %ifag%i. The word <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>pāk</w><gloss><q>omnis</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/><gloss><q>totus</q></gloss></mentioned>,  (alongside with <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>pāk</w><gloss><q>clean</q></gloss></mentioned>) is more close to it from semantic point of view. It is also possible that it was derived from *ap-āka- (from ap- ‘reach’). — <bibl><ref target="#ref_Шегрен"/><biblScope>68</biblScope></bibl>: <mentioned xml:lang="ar"><lang/><w>faqat</w><gloss><q>only</q></gloss></mentioned>.</etym></entry>